      <hedline>
        <hl1>Measure of a Species</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>John E Isom letter, responding to Philip M Boffey's Aug 21 Editorial Observer article, says Brazil's rain forests are being destroyed by our appetite for larger cars, larger homes and larger population</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Brazil's rain forests are being destroyed at twice the rate we thought (Editorial Observer, Aug. 21). Yet our appetite for larger cars, larger homes and a larger population continues. When will we realize that economic growth is not the measure of a successful species?</p>
        <p>JOHN E. ISOM  Madison, Wis., Aug. 21, 2000</p>
      </block>
